docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — On the opening day of a criminal trial testing the sweep of a federal law that regulates lobbying for foreign clients, defense lawyers argued that a prominent Washington lawyer accused of lying about his work for Ukraine’s government was in fact the victim of overzealous prosecutors.

docs.snippet: Mr. Kennedy, the grandson of Robert F. Kennedy, paid for a poll last month to test his prospects against Mr. Markey, a Democratic official said.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Representative Joseph P. Kennedy III of Massachusetts is considering a primary challenge next year against Senator Edward J. Markey, according to a senior Democratic official. Such a race could substantially alter the state’s political landscape and has the potential to elevate a fourth member of a Democratic dynasty to the Senate.

headline.main: Joseph Kennedy III Said to Be Eying Edward Markey’s Massachusetts Senate Seat
headline.print_headline: Joseph Kennedy Is Said to Be Eyeing Markey’s Seat in the Senate

docs.abstract: After making baseless claims of voter fraud, the president has turned to a new way of explaining his loss of the popular vote in 2016.
docs.snippet: After making baseless claims of voter fraud, the president has turned to a new way of explaining his loss of the popular vote in 2016.
docs.lead_paragraph: Mr. Trump lost the popular vote by almost 2.9 million in the 2016 election and has long attributed this loss to baseless claims of voter fraud. Now Mr. Trump suggests that he would have lost the popular vote by a much smaller margin, or even won it, were it not for Google’s machinations.

headline.main: Fact-Checking Trump’s Claim That Google ‘Manipulated’ Millions of Votes for Clinton

docs.abstract: President Trump has signaled displeasure with the American ally. His lawyer has been pressing the government in Kiev to investigate his political foes.
docs.snippet: President Trump has signaled displeasure with the American ally. His lawyer has been pressing the government in Kiev to investigate his political foes.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The White House delayed a package of military assistance to the new government in Ukraine, and has yet to schedule a White House meeting for its new president. After abruptly pulling the previous American ambassador out of Kiev when conservatives questioned her political loyalty, President Trump has yet to nominate a successor.

headline.main: Amid Diplomatic Strain, House Opens Inquiry Into Trump’s Dealings With Ukraine
headline.print_headline: U.S. House Opens Query  Into Trump’s Handling Of Policies for Ukraine

docs.abstract: Investigators placed blame not on the HUD secretary, but on department officials who “were aware of the law” and “either failed to consider or didn’t understand” that it applied to the purchase.

docs.lead_paragraph: Department of Housing and Urban Development investigators found no evidence that Secretary Ben Carson acted improperly when he tried to buy a $31,000 dining room set for his office in 2017, according to an inspector general’s report released on Thursday.

headline.main: Ben Carson Is Cleared of Misconduct Over Order of $31,000 Dining Set

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The White House on Monday blocked two more former aides to President Trump from testifying in House Democrats’ impeachment inquiry, but cleared a third witness, Corey Lewandowski, to appear publicly on Tuesday and answer limited questions about potential obstruction of justice by the president.

headline.main: Lewandowski Cleared for Limited Testimony in House Inquiry, as White House Blocks Others

docs.abstract: Mr. Trump told reporters of the plans after a day of highly critical news coverage as he traveled to the sites of mass shootings in El Paso and Dayton, Ohio, that left 31 dead.

docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — President Trump said on Wednesday night that he was “strongly considering” commuting the 14-year prison sentence of Rod R. Blagojevich, the former Illinois governor who was convicted of trying to essentially sell President Barack Obama’s vacated Senate seat for personal gain.

headline.main: After Strongly Suggesting He May Commute Blagojevich’s Sentence, Trump Says Matter Is Under Review
headline.print_headline: Trump Tempers Support For Imprisoned Governor

docs.abstract: The president became frustrated over his news coverage and his angry reaction led to White House-distributed media that focused on him, not people affected by the shootings.
docs.snippet: The president became frustrated over his news coverage and his angry reaction led to White House-distributed media that focused on him, not people affected by the shootings.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — By the time President Trump arrived in El Paso on Wednesday, on the second leg of a trip to meet with people affected by mass shootings in two cities, he was frustrated that his attacks on his political adversaries had resulted in more coverage than the cheery reception he received at a hospital in Dayton, Ohio, the first stop on his trip. So he screamed at his aides to begin producing proof that in El Paso people were happy to see him.

headline.main: Trump’s Trip to Dayton and El Paso: The Back Story
headline.print_headline: Thumbs Up and All Smiles, the President Strains to Send a Message
